You're not a sexy cat. Stop that.

52:11.890 --> 52:13.721
I'm a bad kitty.

52:13.892 --> 52:16.360
You're not a bad kitty,
you're a sleepy lunatic.

52:16.528 --> 52:20.760
I'm a bad kitty.
I need to have my whiskers licked.

52:20.932 --> 52:23.332
There are no circumstances under which
I'd do that to a cat.

52:24.702 --> 52:27.102
Go to sleep.
That's enough of that. Stop it. Get... Ow!

52:28.473 --> 52:30.600
No! Unh. Ow!

52:34.846 --> 52:36.939
So this must be a fun job.

52:37.515 --> 52:39.642
Yes, it has its moments.

52:39.851 --> 52:43.685
Like trying to protect Arthur
from people with dubious intentions.

52:43.855 --> 52:44.981
NAOMl:
Hmm.

52:47.959 --> 52:50.427
Oh, you mean me.

52:50.595 --> 52:53.758
Because I'm totally after the money,
if that's what you're thinking.

52:53.932 --> 52:56.799
How is the illegal
tour guide business going?

52:57.302 --> 52:58.894
Feeds my dad.

52:59.571 --> 53:02.404
But I'm actually writing a book.
A children's book.

53:03.174 --> 53:04.573
It was Arthur's idea.

53:04.742 --> 53:08.701
Well, make sure there are lots of pictures,
otherwise he won't understand it.

53:08.880 --> 53:11.781
I think Arthur understands
more than you realize.

53:18.487 --> 53:22.321
So, Hobson, are there any men
in your life?

53:22.691 --> 53:25.182
Are you attempting
to make small talk with me?

53:25.394 --> 53:27.954
I am attempting it. Is it working?

53:28.764 --> 53:31.494
- No, not really.
- Darn it.

53:32.334 --> 53:33.426
So?

53:34.904 --> 53:36.371
Any man I've ever met...

53:36.539 --> 53:42.444
...pales in comparison to the dazzling
floor show that is Arthur's company.

53:45.714 --> 53:48.444
I know you were being sarcastic
just then...

53:49.218 --> 53:52.415
...but it really is quite dazzling.

53:52.588 --> 53:55.955
All is fair in love and war, eh, darling?

53:56.125 --> 53:58.252
Do you think he's okay?

53:58.427 --> 53:59.451
Ow! Ow!

53:59.628 --> 54:02.620
- Bad horse.
- Ow! That's not erotic. It just hurts.

54:02.798 --> 54:04.732
No. Susan. Stop it.
You can't do that.

54:04.900 --> 54:07.596
Horses and cats can't mate.
Our children will be monsters.

54:13.442 --> 54:17.071
Hobson, it's not what it looks like.
Unless it looks like a cat raping a horse.

54:21.050 --> 54:22.381
Arthur.

54:22.551 --> 54:23.984
- What's happening?
- Oh.

54:24.153 --> 54:25.552
What has happened to me?

54:25.721 --> 54:28.588
I think the problem is your clothes
are made of metal...

54:28.757 --> 54:31.385
...and my bed is made of magnets.

54:31.560 --> 54:34.120
- Oh, you think so?
- Right. Okay. Uh, stay calm, kitty.

54:34.296 --> 54:36.321
I'm not a cat anymore.
I am a businesswoman.

54:36.499 --> 54:38.524
I think I have a remote control.
Excuse me.

54:38.701 --> 54:41.693
- Uh... Ah, right. I've got the remote.
- Get me off of here!

54:41.871 --> 54:43.805
Okay, I'm coming.
I'm gonna... Ah, got it.

54:43.973 --> 54:46.567
- What are you doing?
- Okay, it's not that, obviously.

54:46.742 --> 54:50.200
Uh, on the bright side, at least something
in this room is attracted to you.

54:50.379 --> 54:51.676
For the love of God.

54:51.847 --> 54:53.007
Maybe this.

54:54.583 --> 54:57.143
- Oh, are you all right?
- Not that.

54:57.319 --> 54:58.946
I'm not gonna press this anymore...

54:59.121 --> 55:02.887
...because if I press the wrong button,
the bed could fall and kill you.

55:03.058 --> 55:05.322
Which none of us would want.
None of us.

55:05.828 --> 55:07.955
I've gotta go and get Hobson.
She knows how this works.

55:08.130 --> 55:12.726
Oh, you are a useless man. You can't do
anything without that miserable old woman.

55:16.805 --> 55:18.033
There you are.

55:18.674 --> 55:20.403
That was a lot of primping.

55:20.576 --> 55:23.136
Oh, ha, yeah, yeah.
Primping. Yeah, primping.

55:23.312 --> 55:25.872
Yeah, it's primpalicious, though,
isn't it? The results.

55:26.048 --> 55:27.538
He's a primpanzee.

55:27.716 --> 55:31.846
Sorry about this noise.
I think it's, um... It's the bloody neighbors.

55:32.021 --> 55:34.455
- Neighbors?
- Well, I think I'll retire now.

55:34.623 --> 55:35.920
Good night, Hobson.

55:36.091 --> 55:39.618
Ahem. Hobson.
Um, thank you for everything.

55:39.795 --> 55:40.853
I did it for her.

55:41.030 --> 55:42.554
I don't want that poor girl humiliated.

55:42.731 --> 55:47.259
- You like her, don't you? She's lovely.
- Just be a grown-up for once, Arthur.

55:47.436 --> 55:49.233
Okay.

55:50.372 --> 55:55.833
Oh, um, could you detach the half-naked
businesswoman from under my bed?

55:56.111 --> 55:57.806
Sorry.

55:59.315 --> 56:00.475
Good night, Hobson.

56:00.649 --> 56:02.412
Goodbye, Naomi.

56:06.188 --> 56:07.678
NAOMl:
Not a bad back yard.

56:07.856 --> 56:10.950
Yes, except whenever I sunbathe nude,
I get the strangest looks.

56:11.126 --> 56:12.423
Oh, you're that guy.

56:12.595 --> 56:15.029
- Are you a bit chilly?
- Oh, yes.

56:15.197 --> 56:18.064
- Would you like?
- Thank you.

56:18.233 --> 56:20.064
Ahem, here.

56:20.436 --> 56:23.371
- Is this your father's? "Gerald Bach. "
It is.

56:23.572 --> 56:27.838
Well, it was. I had some of his suits
re-tailored to fit me.

56:28.010 --> 56:30.535
It seemed silly to throw them away.

56:32.014 --> 56:34.346
Mm.
- Oh.

56:34.516 --> 56:36.313
"Why bother taking care of yourself?"

56:36.485 --> 56:39.045
Ha, ha. Yeah. Just have fun.

56:39.221 --> 56:41.348
- Well, you seem to have a lot of fun.
- It's my calling.

56:42.725 --> 56:45.353
I found a free thing to show you.
It's this way.

56:45.527 --> 56:47.495
- Come with me. Come on.
- Okay.

56:48.664 --> 56:53.499
In my mind, this is the pond
from a book I had when I was a kid...

56:53.669 --> 56:55.500
...called Frog and Toad Together.

56:55.671 --> 56:58.834
I love Frog and Toad. My mom used to
read them to me all the time.

56:59.008 --> 57:00.134
- Really?
- Yeah.

57:00.309 --> 57:02.641
My mom subcontracted
that job to Hobson.

57:02.811 --> 57:08.249
NAOMl: There's a really sad one
where Toad freaks out...

57:08.417 --> 57:11.978
...because he sees Frog sitting alone
on a rock.

57:12.154 --> 57:16.488
So he swims out to him with a picnic,
but then it falls in the water.

57:16.659 --> 57:18.149
"Our lunch is spoiled.

57:18.327 --> 57:20.887
I made it for you, Frog,
so you'd be happy. "

57:21.063 --> 57:23.054
But Frog wasn't sad.

57:23.899 --> 57:25.730
"When I woke up, I felt good...

57:25.901 --> 57:29.359
...because the sun was shining.
I felt good because I was a frog. "

57:30.572 --> 57:33.735
And I felt good
because I have you for a friend.

57:36.278 --> 57:39.179
If you were sitting alone,
I'd bring you a sandwich.

57:40.716 --> 57:42.707
I'll sit alone, then.

57:59.935 --> 58:03.803
"And Frog and Toad
stayed on the island all afternoon.

58:03.972 --> 58:07.965
They ate wet sandwiches
without iced tea.

58:08.877 --> 58:13.041
They were two close friends
sitting alone together. "

58:16.618 --> 58:18.677
I couldn't tell her, Hobson.

58:18.887 --> 58:20.582
She's my Toad.

58:20.756 --> 58:22.621
Oh, bollocks.

58:23.992 --> 58:27.655
Listen, Arthur, I'm sure Naomi
is a very nice girl...

58:27.830 --> 58:30.128
...but you can't live
without the money.

58:30.899 --> 58:32.366
How do you know?

58:32.534 --> 58:36.197
Please. You can't go half an hour
without buying another sports car.

58:37.773 --> 58:39.764
When I was little you used to say:

58:39.942 --> 58:42.672
"Arthur,
you can do anything under the sun. "

58:42.845 --> 58:44.142
I never spoke like that.

58:44.313 --> 58:45.439
It was a bit like that.

58:45.614 --> 58:47.980
That was before
you paid Elton John $2 million...

58:48.150 --> 58:50.380
...to sing over the PA in a grocery store.

58:50.986 --> 58:52.715
Yeah, well, it was Easter.

58:53.522 --> 58:57.117
- I think I could live without the money.
- Oh, yes? How?

58:58.360 --> 58:59.452
I'd get a job.

58:59.628 --> 59:01.596
- Ha!
- What?

59:02.798 --> 59:07.132
Fine. Fine. Go ahead. Get a job.

59:08.103 --> 59:09.627
I am a grown man...

59:09.805 --> 59:14.105
...and I shall join the mature world
of gainful employment to prove it.

59:17.446 --> 59:20.415
Don't let that undermine
what I just said.

59:32.127 --> 59:34.595
- Do you know how to use Excel?
- No.

59:34.763 --> 59:36.788
- PowerPoint?
- No.

59:37.833 --> 59:40.301
- Outlook.
- Generally positive. You know, I mean...

59:40.469 --> 59:43.199
...I have down days like anyone, but...
It's a program.

59:43.372 --> 59:45.203
Oh, um, no.

59:46.241 --> 59:47.265
Can you file?

59:47.442 --> 59:48.466
- File?
Yes.

59:48.644 --> 59:50.111
In a?

59:51.213 --> 59:52.237
No.

59:53.816 --> 59:55.716
There must be something I can do.

59:58.821 --> 59:59.845
Hey!

01:00:00.022 --> 01:00:02.115
And so, this is how you simply sign on...

01:00:02.291 --> 01:00:03.849
...and that unlocks the register.

01:00:04.026 --> 01:00:08.827
Now, you clock in, employee number,
password and the register's yours.

01:00:09.565 --> 01:00:11.726
This, uh, might seem a bit much
for my first day...

01:00:11.900 --> 01:00:14.801
...but could I inquire as to the possibility
of a transfer...

01:00:14.970 --> 01:00:16.801
...to the costume-greeter department?

01:00:16.972 --> 01:00:18.030
I think I'd thrive.

01:00:18.207 --> 01:00:20.835
No. Let's just start
with the register for you.

01:00:21.043 --> 01:00:22.908
I've got my own costume, if that helps.

01:00:23.078 --> 01:00:25.069
Nope, doesn't really make
a difference. No.

01:00:25.247 --> 01:00:26.544
Register. So I've cleared it.

01:00:26.715 --> 01:00:29.081
Go ahead and enter your
employee number and log in.

01:00:30.452 --> 01:00:33.819
- Okay. You just hit a lot of random keys.
- Well, that's what you did, in fairness.

01:00:35.190 --> 01:00:37.590
- It says "invalid key. "
- Yes. Invalid key.

01:00:37.759 --> 01:00:39.488
That means that I need to reset this.

01:00:39.661 --> 01:00:42.687
This may take a moment.
Would you mind just stepping right over?

01:00:42.865 --> 01:00:46.528
How did he get that job, exactly? What
is he, the owner? The son of the owner?

01:00:46.702 --> 01:00:49.899
- You can't do it, and you never will.
- Never?

01:00:50.072 --> 01:00:51.096
That's harsh.

01:00:51.273 --> 01:00:53.605
I've entered
your employee number and... Oh.

01:00:53.775 --> 01:00:55.174
Want some?

01:00:55.444 --> 01:00:58.413
- I think you should take the day off.
- As a reward?

01:00:58.981 --> 01:01:01.040
Tomorrow we'll find
something more suitable for you.

01:01:01.216 --> 01:01:03.707
I think what he's doing is derivative.

01:01:11.026 --> 01:01:13.051
Oh, the moon really is following me.

01:01:13.228 --> 01:01:16.129
Would you stop going on about the moon
following you?

01:01:17.532 --> 01:01:18.624
He's lunar.

01:01:18.800 --> 01:01:19.824
He's clearly a pervert.

01:01:32.347 --> 01:01:35.783
Arthur? There've been some reports
of staff members eating on the floor.

01:01:35.951 --> 01:01:37.213
Do you know anything about that?

01:01:37.386 --> 01:01:38.876
Um, no.

01:01:39.054 --> 01:01:41.284
No, I don't know anything
about that, Peter.

01:01:41.456 --> 01:01:44.152
You know, I think it's not appropriate
for you to be on the floor.

01:01:44.326 --> 01:01:46.886
We should find something
for you in the stock room.

01:01:50.632 --> 01:01:51.656
Excuse me.

01:01:52.935 --> 01:01:56.268
If I gave you $10,000...

01:01:56.438 --> 01:01:59.669
...would you let me wear this costume
for one hour?

01:02:01.343 --> 01:02:05.939
Hello. Welcome to the store.
May all your dreams come true.

01:02:06.114 --> 01:02:07.979
Free candy! Here you go, kids!

01:02:09.451 --> 01:02:11.316
I'm a lovely bear. Grr.

01:02:12.688 --> 01:02:15.179
Sorry. Sorry. I'm not a genuine bear.

01:02:15.357 --> 01:02:17.825
Here, listen, you take this with you.

01:02:17.993 --> 01:02:22.123
If you leave very quickly, security won't
have an opportunity to ascertain you.

01:02:22.297 --> 01:02:24.197
- Go. Try not to look suspicious.
- Arthur?

01:02:24.366 --> 01:02:25.628
- Hello.
- What are you doing?

01:02:25.801 --> 01:02:27.598
Peter, I can explain everything.

01:02:29.438 --> 01:02:31.531
I've got one. I'm okay.

01:02:34.643 --> 01:02:35.667
Arthur.

01:02:37.179 --> 01:02:40.512
- May I have a word with you?
- Is that word "promotion"?

01:02:41.917 --> 01:02:45.250
One apocalyptic hangover, no job.

01:02:45.721 --> 01:02:47.621
Congratulations, Arthur.

01:02:50.125 --> 01:02:53.026
The employment market is a vortex.

01:02:53.195 --> 01:02:58.497
Listen to this: "Aquarium needs help
cleaning tanks. Swim with the fishes. "

01:02:58.700 --> 01:02:59.997
That is a Mob threat.

01:03:00.202 --> 01:03:02.534
None of these jobs make any sense at all.

01:03:02.704 --> 01:03:05.502
"Systems integration professional. "

01:03:05.707 --> 01:03:07.334
Would anyone do it as an amateur?

01:03:07.509 --> 01:03:09.500
Would anyone approach
systems integration...

01:03:09.678 --> 01:03:12.943
...as a hobby for fun on a Saturday
afternoon instead of flying a kite?

01:03:13.115 --> 01:03:16.573
Who is integrating systems
for their own amusement?

01:03:17.919 --> 01:03:18.977
Hobson.

01:03:20.155 --> 01:03:23.591
I think in order to do this...

01:03:23.759 --> 01:03:26.489
...I may have to be a little more sober.

01:03:31.466 --> 01:03:32.933
What do you think?

01:03:33.101 --> 01:03:36.036
To, you know, preserve my anonymity.

01:03:37.005 --> 01:03:39.337
You're right,
it would be a shame to jeopardize...

01:03:39.508 --> 01:03:42.102
...such a distinguished public profile.

01:03:50.185 --> 01:03:53.052
I stole from my friends, my family.

01:03:53.622 --> 01:03:56.386
I sold my son's tricycle
so I could score some junk.

01:03:57.059 --> 01:03:58.959
- Jesus.
I was so drunk once...

01:03:59.127 --> 01:04:01.994
...I backed my car
over my mother outside Walgreens.

01:04:02.164 --> 01:04:03.222
Thirty-seven days sober.

01:04:04.599 --> 01:04:07.295
But sometimes, it's just so hard.

01:04:07.469 --> 01:04:09.027
Like I'm in this grave...

01:04:09.204 --> 01:04:13.072
Whoa, this is depressing.
It's like unhappy hour.

01:04:13.241 --> 01:04:14.936
- Shh.
- It is. I don't like it in here.

01:04:15.110 --> 01:04:16.634
This is making me want to drink more.

01:04:16.812 --> 01:04:20.304
Sir, you need to wait till the end
of the meeting. Go on, James.

01:04:20.715 --> 01:04:22.046
It's okay. I'm done.

01:04:23.418 --> 01:04:24.612
And you are?

01:04:26.154 --> 01:04:28.884
My name is...

01:04:29.091 --> 01:04:30.820
...Gandalf.

01:04:30.992 --> 01:04:32.789
Hi, Gandalf.

01:04:33.228 --> 01:04:34.991
Hello.

01:04:35.397 --> 01:04:40.733
And I came here because I'd like to drink
a bit less. Not give it up altogether.

01:04:40.902 --> 01:04:43.530
Maybe 5, 10 percent cut down.
Reasonable.

01:04:43.705 --> 01:04:48.836
Look, I'm sorry. No one's gonna convince
me that my life isn't fun, okay?

01:04:49.010 --> 01:04:51.478
And forgive my crassness...

01:04:51.646 --> 01:04:55.742
...but if I ran my mother over,
I'd be out celebrating with booze.

01:04:56.184 --> 01:05:00.052
Which is what I plan to do right now.

01:05:00.222 --> 01:05:01.655
Cheerio.

01:05:01.823 --> 01:05:04.189
Excuse me. Hobson.

01:05:06.128 --> 01:05:08.596
My name is Lillian and I'm an alcoholic.

01:05:08.763 --> 01:05:10.060
Hi, Lillian.

01:05:10.232 --> 01:05:11.699
Good afternoon.

01:05:11.867 --> 01:05:14.301
I'm rich. I'm fabulously rich.

01:05:15.036 --> 01:05:17.698
I'm also generous and kindhearted.

01:05:18.740 --> 01:05:23.109
My father died when I was young and
my mother was absent most of the time.

01:05:23.278 --> 01:05:27.078
Is this an excuse for making a mockery
of my life?

01:05:27.382 --> 01:05:30.112
Oh, sure, it all looks very wild
from the outside.

01:05:30.285 --> 01:05:34.312
Do you know, I once went to bed with three
European princesses at the same time.

01:05:34.489 --> 01:05:36.320
But, A, I can't remember anything
about it...

01:05:36.491 --> 01:05:38.425
...and, B, apparently,
I vomited on two of them...

01:05:38.593 --> 01:05:40.959
...before losing control of my bladder
on the third.

01:05:41.129 --> 01:05:43.654
Oh, yes, all such fun.

01:05:43.832 --> 01:05:47.097
Until the fog parts,
and suddenly there's a hole so big...

01:05:47.269 --> 01:05:52.571
...that all the vintage champagne
and the Batmobiles in the world won't fill it.

01:05:52.741 --> 01:05:56.905
And then? Well, then,
I'm all alone on my magnetic bed...

01:05:57.078 --> 01:06:00.912
...wondering what venereal disease
I've just caught.

01:06:08.290 --> 01:06:10.417
Always the quiet ones.

01:06:15.163 --> 01:06:17.461
This is itchy.

01:06:27.542 --> 01:06:31.444
That was really lovely what you said
in there about me.

01:06:32.847 --> 01:06:37.841
Now, if you could just do the drinking for
me, I think we'd have this thing cracked.

01:06:54.369 --> 01:06:56.997
Vivienne.
Yes?

01:06:58.139 --> 01:07:00.300
Don't make me do this, please.

01:07:01.843 --> 01:07:03.743
I'm not the one with a choice.

01:07:03.945 --> 01:07:05.970
You can walk away any time you like.

01:07:06.147 --> 01:07:08.741
There's a simple solution
to all of this, Arthur.

01:07:08.950 --> 01:07:11.612
Marry Susan
and cheat with the nobody from Queens.

01:07:41.182 --> 01:07:43.980
Hello, Naomi's dad.
Is your daughter here?

01:07:44.152 --> 01:07:46.780
Her name is Naomi.
Just clear up any confusion.

01:07:46.955 --> 01:07:50.186
It's a little late, but I wasn't
sleeping myself. Come in, come in.

01:07:50.358 --> 01:07:51.450
Arthur?

01:07:52.027 --> 01:07:54.291
Oh, hello, Naomi.

01:07:58.199 --> 01:08:00.099
You may wanna sit down.

01:08:03.204 --> 01:08:04.262
Or lay down.

01:08:04.439 --> 01:08:07.033
Although I prefer you stayed awake,
because this is important.

01:08:07.409 --> 01:08:08.501
What is it?

01:08:09.010 --> 01:08:11.308
I'm engaged to another Susan.

01:08:11.513 --> 01:08:13.947
Woman. Another Susan woman.

01:08:15.583 --> 01:08:17.015
You're engaged?

01:08:17.185 --> 01:08:20.814
I'm so sorry I didn't tell you.
I meant to before.

01:08:21.022 --> 01:08:23.889
You meant to tell me that you were
engaged to another woman.

01:08:24.059 --> 01:08:28.496
- I was gonna get Hobson to do it...
- Oh, my God. Arthur.

01:08:28.662 --> 01:08:30.187
- Who do you think you are?
- Naomi.

01:08:30.965 --> 01:08:33.263
I'm not saying I think I'm Naomi.
You are.

01:08:33.435 --> 01:08:35.335
Why else would you be wearing
her pajamas.

01:08:35.737 --> 01:08:39.173
I didn't mean for this to happen,
but then I started falling for you.

01:08:39.341 --> 01:08:41.639
And I thought,
"Oh, no. I'm falling for Naomi...

01:08:41.810 --> 01:08:44.643
...and I have to marry Susan woman
or I'll lose the money. "

01:08:45.246 --> 01:08:48.180
Let me get this straight.
You don't wanna marry this woman.

01:08:48.350 --> 01:08:51.113
- Susan woman.
- But you're going to...

01:08:51.286 --> 01:08:53.515
