Hmm, Hobson.

01:27:51.825 --> 01:27:53.690
I had a bad dream.

01:27:53.861 --> 01:27:55.658
Hobson?

01:27:57.164 --> 01:27:59.724
Hobson, stop mucking about.

01:27:59.967 --> 01:28:03.334
You can't see a tunnel of light
and red pitchfork.

01:28:03.504 --> 01:28:07.133
I'm not gonna take those three books
back to the library.

01:28:10.010 --> 01:28:11.875
Hobson?

01:28:17.417 --> 01:28:19.214
Nurse!

01:28:19.386 --> 01:28:21.217
Nurse!

01:29:24.451 --> 01:29:26.248
Bitterman?

01:29:31.391 --> 01:29:33.484
We're gonna have a party.

01:29:33.660 --> 01:29:35.924
I'm tired of being sad now.

01:30:29.950 --> 01:30:32.077
Bitterman, what are you doing?

01:30:32.252 --> 01:30:35.016
I'm trying to cheer you up, Mr. Bach.

01:30:35.188 --> 01:30:36.280
Is it working?

01:30:37.557 --> 01:30:38.615
Not yet.

01:30:42.796 --> 01:30:43.888
How about now?

01:30:44.631 --> 01:30:47.327
You have to do something funny.
You can't just stand there.

01:30:47.501 --> 01:30:51.403
- Just say something incongruous or pithy.
- Okay.

01:30:52.039 --> 01:30:54.234
Today's your wedding day, Mr. Bach.

01:30:54.408 --> 01:30:56.968
Well, that's it. I'm gonna drown myself.

01:30:57.444 --> 01:30:59.002
Mr. Bach?

01:30:59.179 --> 01:31:01.079
Mr. Bach? Where'd you go?

01:31:02.749 --> 01:31:05.718
Lovely to see you. Hello.

01:31:06.853 --> 01:31:08.252
Chancellor.

01:31:08.422 --> 01:31:11.118
- I am so delighted you're here.
- Oh, thank you.

01:31:11.291 --> 01:31:14.454
I think you'll be very, very pleasantly
surprised. Enjoy yourself.

01:31:14.628 --> 01:31:15.720
The groom is here.

01:31:15.896 --> 01:31:19.923
Ah. I gather the groom has arrived.

01:31:20.100 --> 01:31:21.897
Bitterman. Bitterman.

01:31:22.536 --> 01:31:25.004
Please. I'm getting married today.

01:31:25.172 --> 01:31:27.333
But you were in there too long.

01:31:27.841 --> 01:31:30.810
- Oh, God. She's here.
- You're late. Was I not clear?

01:31:30.977 --> 01:31:33.537
Don't... Don't... Don't blame Bitterman.

01:31:33.714 --> 01:31:36.512
He had a hell of a struggle getting me
out of the bath.

01:31:36.750 --> 01:31:37.842
Coffee. Now.

01:31:38.018 --> 01:31:39.815
Good idea. I'll have one too.

01:31:39.986 --> 01:31:41.078
I'm a bit drunk.

01:31:41.254 --> 01:31:42.721
Okay.

01:31:42.889 --> 01:31:45.187
The good news is you're here
and you're not wearing a cape.

01:31:45.358 --> 01:31:47.349
Proud day for you, Viv?

01:31:48.995 --> 01:31:51.623
I have guests to attend to. Stay.

01:32:28.735 --> 01:32:30.202
Psst.

01:32:30.570 --> 01:32:32.538
Small person.

01:32:33.206 --> 01:32:34.571
Can you read?

01:32:35.442 --> 01:32:37.501
For, like, four years. Can you?

01:32:37.811 --> 01:32:39.745
Not at the moment, no.

01:32:39.913 --> 01:32:40.937
Help. Come here.

01:32:50.457 --> 01:32:52.357
I need you to read this for me.

01:32:52.926 --> 01:32:54.518
Okay.

01:32:59.065 --> 01:33:04.469
"My dearest Arthur.
Listen up, you pampered prick. "

01:33:04.638 --> 01:33:06.401
Carry on.

01:33:06.573 --> 01:33:08.666
"You now know where the tea bags are.

01:33:08.842 --> 01:33:11.436
To operate kettle, press red button.

01:33:11.711 --> 01:33:13.235
Milk in refrigerator.

01:33:13.413 --> 01:33:17.008
That's the big box with the pretty light
that comes on when you open the door.

01:33:17.717 --> 01:33:21.881
It's not too late, Arthur.
You can do anything under the sun.

01:33:22.055 --> 01:33:24.683
All my deepest, fondest love.

01:33:24.858 --> 01:33:26.849
I'm smiling down at you.

01:33:27.027 --> 01:33:30.019
Or, more likely, up at you.

01:33:30.597 --> 01:33:34.158
Forever and ever, H."

01:33:39.606 --> 01:33:40.834
Are you crying?

01:33:42.342 --> 01:33:45.334
That's a bride's job, to cry.

01:33:45.512 --> 01:33:47.241
It's time to man up, Arthur.

01:34:28.622 --> 01:34:29.680
Dearly beloved...

01:34:30.557 --> 01:34:35.585
...we are gathered here today
to join Arthur and Susan in matrimony.

01:34:36.563 --> 01:34:40.465
Which is commended
to be honorable among all men.

01:34:40.634 --> 01:34:46.834
And therefore, is not by any to be entered
into unadvisedly or lightly...

01:34:47.040 --> 01:34:50.840
...but reverently, discreetly and solemnly.

01:34:51.011 --> 01:34:54.139
Seems like a lot of adverbs.
That seem like a lot of adverbs to you?

01:34:54.314 --> 01:34:55.645
Shh, Arthur.

01:34:55.815 --> 01:34:59.148
If any person can show just cause...

01:34:59.452 --> 01:35:02.649
...why they may not
be joined together...

01:35:02.822 --> 01:35:06.758
...let him speak now
or forever hold his peace.

01:35:13.166 --> 01:35:14.292
I object!

01:35:15.902 --> 01:35:19.736
To this wedding.
- Arthur, you can't object. It's your wedding.

01:35:19.906 --> 01:35:24.400
Is it my wedding? Because I think if it was,
I'd know who all these people were.

01:35:24.577 --> 01:35:25.976
I mean, who are you?

01:35:26.279 --> 01:35:28.474
- I'm your best man.
- I've never seen you befor...

01:35:28.648 --> 01:35:32.106
- Actually, have I? I recognize you a bit.
- I'm your mother's receptionist.

01:35:32.285 --> 01:35:34.253
Oh, yeah, right. It's nice to see you.

01:35:34.421 --> 01:35:37.117
But what about you two?
Who's Abercrombie and who's Fitch?

01:35:37.290 --> 01:35:39.815
And was there a bachelor party?
I wasn't invited.

01:35:39.993 --> 01:35:43.656
If there was, then I don't think
I'd have enjoyed it. You look like squares.

01:35:43.830 --> 01:35:45.798
And I've slept with three of them.

01:35:46.099 --> 01:35:48.260
Not sure which three.
I just... Statistically...

01:35:48.435 --> 01:35:50.767
Susan, this isn't real.

01:35:50.937 --> 01:35:54.270
This wedding is a sham. It's a
wonderful sham wedding, but it's a sham.

01:35:54.441 --> 01:35:56.033
We don't love each other.

01:35:56.209 --> 01:35:58.769
Even you deserve better than this.

01:36:02.716 --> 01:36:05.810
In fact, it was Abraham Lincoln
who said, "Freedom... "

01:36:07.687 --> 01:36:08.711
That's my little girl.

01:36:12.292 --> 01:36:15.227
- You will marry me.
- No, Susan. Abercrombie. Fitch.

01:36:15.395 --> 01:36:20.731
I am the future of this company,
and all I need is your goddamn last name.

01:36:22.802 --> 01:36:24.326
- Hit him in the face.
- No.

01:36:24.504 --> 01:36:26.472
Stop.

01:36:26.639 --> 01:36:28.573
Don't touch my son.

01:36:31.378 --> 01:36:33.312
But Vivienne.

01:36:33.546 --> 01:36:35.741
I think you've said enough.

01:36:36.116 --> 01:36:37.140
Arthur, come here.

01:36:47.694 --> 01:36:49.321
Are you certain about this?

01:36:50.063 --> 01:36:51.758
Yes, I am.

01:36:52.165 --> 01:36:53.689
It means giving up everything.

01:36:54.968 --> 01:36:57.528
I'm happy to give up everything.

01:36:58.071 --> 01:37:02.371
In fact, Vivienne, I can start
giving up everything right now.

01:37:02.542 --> 01:37:05.705
This, for example.
Don't need that where I'm going.

01:37:05.879 --> 01:37:08.370
Blue-collar district.
This will look sarcastic.

01:37:08.548 --> 01:37:11.949
I feel like I'm bound up
like a little Japanese girl's foot.

01:37:12.118 --> 01:37:15.918
I don't want that on anymore.
Shackles, chaining me to wealth.

01:37:16.089 --> 01:37:17.454
Bloody thing. Ugh.

01:37:18.158 --> 01:37:20.388
This shirt, itchy.

01:37:20.560 --> 01:37:22.084
I don't want it anymore.

01:37:22.262 --> 01:37:25.288
I can assure all of you that after this...

01:37:25.465 --> 01:37:28.696
...I will be nowhere near the Bach fund.

01:37:28.868 --> 01:37:32.065
So your investments are on solid footing.

01:37:34.641 --> 01:37:38.202
Excuse me. Don't let that detract
from what I just said.

01:37:38.378 --> 01:37:39.606
And finally...

01:37:41.748 --> 01:37:46.014
Actually, um, these were
a Christmas present from Hobson. I...

01:37:46.219 --> 01:37:47.777
I think I'll hang onto them.

01:37:47.954 --> 01:37:51.151
- I'm keeping this ring. I'm keeping this ring.
- Yes.

01:37:51.324 --> 01:37:54.555
Okay, well, uh, I'm going to be poor now.

01:38:01.768 --> 01:38:02.894
So how'd it go?

01:38:03.369 --> 01:38:08.136
Well, um, I'm very sorry, Bitterman,
but I'm afraid you're out of a job.

01:38:10.143 --> 01:38:11.167
Congratulations.

01:38:12.178 --> 01:38:15.375
- Is there anywhere I could take you, sir?
- Well, that's very sweet...

01:38:15.548 --> 01:38:18.210
...but I've gotta get used to fending
for myself now.

01:38:18.384 --> 01:38:20.784
Could you hail me a cab, please?

01:38:23.356 --> 01:38:25.290
Arthur.

01:38:29.829 --> 01:38:32.161
- Once again, you've humiliated me.
- Sorry.

01:38:32.332 --> 01:38:36.291
But this time, I respect you for it.

01:38:36.469 --> 01:38:38.130
You're stronger than I thought.

01:38:38.338 --> 01:38:40.499
And you've shown me the truth
about Susan.

01:38:40.673 --> 01:38:42.368
Yeah, she's bloody evil, isn't she?

01:38:42.542 --> 01:38:44.032
Oh.

01:38:45.078 --> 01:38:47.308
- For the cab.
- Oh.

01:38:47.480 --> 01:38:49.277
Good luck in your life, Arthur.

01:38:51.818 --> 01:38:53.342
A bit awkward.

01:38:54.721 --> 01:38:56.052
We've got to get to Queens.

01:38:56.222 --> 01:38:57.849
Do you know Queens?

01:38:58.024 --> 01:39:00.720
It's full of traffic, isn't it?

01:39:04.030 --> 01:39:05.327
Do you know Naomi?

01:39:05.498 --> 01:39:07.159
Mazel tov, I'm looking for Naomi.

01:39:07.333 --> 01:39:08.891
Naomi!

01:39:09.068 --> 01:39:10.160
What?

01:39:11.538 --> 01:39:16.601
Hello. I remembered.
I remembered the bricks and the train.

01:39:16.809 --> 01:39:18.174
I came in a taxi.

01:39:18.745 --> 01:39:21.236
- You're wasted, Arthur.
No!

01:39:21.414 --> 01:39:24.906
Well, yes. But that was only
so I could get married.

01:39:25.084 --> 01:39:29.851
- Oh, okay.
- Naomi! I didn't go through with it.

01:39:30.023 --> 01:39:35.325
Instead, I did the only rational thing,
and I gave away all of my clothes.

01:39:35.495 --> 01:39:39.226
Do you remember one word
of the last conversation we had, Arthur?

01:39:39.399 --> 01:39:44.928
- Yeah, we were going to build a secret door.
- No. The other conversation.

01:39:45.205 --> 01:39:48.504
I gave away billions of money for you.

01:39:48.942 --> 01:39:51.410
You shouldn't have done that.

01:39:53.046 --> 01:39:54.673
Naomi?

01:39:57.750 --> 01:39:59.980
My mum's dead.

01:40:00.920 --> 01:40:02.547
I know.

01:40:03.423 --> 01:40:07.621
And I am so... I'm so, so sorry.

01:40:07.794 --> 01:40:09.227
But...

01:40:09.996 --> 01:40:12.590
...I can't be her replacement.

01:40:14.234 --> 01:40:15.792
Okay.

01:40:53.039 --> 01:40:54.631
I used to have in my apartment...

01:40:54.807 --> 01:40:59.210
...a rather large,
incredibly decadent magnetic bed.

01:40:59.412 --> 01:41:01.812
Thought "This bed is gonna
make me truly happy. "

01:41:01.981 --> 01:41:05.610
This is the one thing that my life requires,
is a floating magnetic bed.

01:41:05.785 --> 01:41:10.347
When I get that, I'll be happy.
And my companion that evening was, um...

01:41:10.523 --> 01:41:14.550
What's a euphemistic way to say it
that doesn't sound unpleasant? Um...

01:41:14.727 --> 01:41:15.751
A prostitute. And...

01:41:17.130 --> 01:41:19.428
We tried to prize open the door
of the fish tank...

01:41:19.599 --> 01:41:21.658
...because we thought
we could make a phone call.

01:41:21.834 --> 01:41:24.598
Broke the door off of the fish tank.

01:41:24.771 --> 01:41:26.898
The fish came flooding out.
I nearly drowned.

01:41:28.541 --> 01:41:32.671
It wasn't without its amusing moments,
but it took a spiritual toll on me...

01:41:32.845 --> 01:41:37.748
...and none of these phone boxes, nor
magnetic beds could fill the hole within me.

01:41:37.950 --> 01:41:41.943
I spent a lot of my life embarrassing
my family and people that care about me.

01:41:42.121 --> 01:41:45.989
But I've made amends with my mother
now. As much as you can with a dragon.

01:41:46.159 --> 01:41:48.024
I'm six months clean today.

01:41:49.829 --> 01:41:51.820
Congratulations.

01:41:52.065 --> 01:41:54.590
I think this is the most
I've ever valued a coin.

01:42:15.988 --> 01:42:17.580
Next.

01:42:17.757 --> 01:42:19.418
Next in line, please.

01:42:23.062 --> 01:42:25.053
That's 12.50.

01:42:37.210 --> 01:42:40.475
NAOMl: Lady Liberty wrapped
her giant green arms...

01:42:40.646 --> 01:42:42.944
...around the Chrysler Building
one last time.

01:42:43.116 --> 01:42:46.711
And then she carefully walked
back to her own island.

01:42:46.886 --> 01:42:49.013
Even though they'll
always live apart...

01:42:49.188 --> 01:42:53.090
...they'll still stand a little taller
and shine a little brighter...

01:42:53.626 --> 01:42:55.890
...because they shared an adventure.

01:42:56.396 --> 01:42:57.420
The end.

01:43:00.199 --> 01:43:03.032
It's question time.
Does anybody have any questions?

01:43:03.202 --> 01:43:04.260
I have a question.

01:43:06.239 --> 01:43:10.972
Does anybody mind
if I tell another story?

01:43:11.144 --> 01:43:12.304
- I mind.
- Me too.

01:43:12.745 --> 01:43:14.645
You sound like Harry Potter.

01:43:14.814 --> 01:43:17.612
Yeah, well, is that a bad thing?
He's a great wizard.

01:43:17.784 --> 01:43:21.447
Listen, it's quite a good story,
and if no one here minds...

01:43:21.621 --> 01:43:22.645
Uh, excuse me, sorry.

01:43:22.822 --> 01:43:26.883
- I'd really like the opportunity
to tell it.

01:43:27.059 --> 01:43:29.527
If that's okay, um...

01:43:30.062 --> 01:43:34.590
Once upon a time, there was a prince.
Handsome, he was.

01:43:34.934 --> 01:43:37.266
He fell in love with a princess
from Queens.

01:43:37.437 --> 01:43:39.667
- Are you a girl or a boy?
- Doesn't matter.

01:43:40.273 --> 01:43:43.470
The fact is,
he loved this princess so much...

01:43:43.643 --> 01:43:46.407
...that he was prepared
to give up his kingdom for her...

01:43:46.579 --> 01:43:48.672
...but she turned him away.

01:43:48.881 --> 01:43:51.748
- What a bitch.
- She was not. Why would you say that?

01:43:51.918 --> 01:43:53.783
She did the right thing,
it turns out...

01:43:53.953 --> 01:43:59.186
...because this prince
had a little bit of a problem with...

01:44:00.159 --> 01:44:03.822
...candy. He couldn't get enough candy.

01:44:03.996 --> 01:44:06.328
- Do you mean drugs?
No. No. Where did you grow up?

01:44:06.499 --> 01:44:07.659
Meth?
- No.

01:44:07.834 --> 01:44:09.597
Crack?
- No. It was just booze.

01:44:09.769 --> 01:44:12.636
Look, this isn't working. Okay.

01:44:16.209 --> 01:44:21.670
What I came here to say to you,
Naomi, is that I'm sorry.

01:44:22.148 --> 01:44:24.309
I'm sorry that I lied to you.

01:44:24.484 --> 01:44:26.884
I'm sorry that I hurt you.

01:44:27.053 --> 01:44:29.851
And I'm sorry
that I asked you to take care of me...

01:44:30.022 --> 01:44:35.153
...when what I want more than anything
in the world is to take care of you.

01:44:39.999 --> 01:44:42.968
And I think that's the end of the story.

01:44:59.285 --> 01:45:01.310
Ew!

01:45:02.755 --> 01:45:04.052
Hey, what's wrong with you?

01:45:04.223 --> 01:45:08.250
This is just two adults
kissing in a room full of children.

01:45:12.031 --> 01:45:13.760
So how's the real world treating you?

01:45:13.933 --> 01:45:17.096
Oh, I've learned mostly that I should
just try and live simply now.

01:45:17.270 --> 01:45:19.204
- It's better for me.
- What is this?

01:45:19.372 --> 01:45:20.896
Bitterman! Why?

01:45:21.073 --> 01:45:25.373
You said, "This is the girl I can buy
back with a fleet of movie cars. "

01:45:25.545 --> 01:45:30.141
I said this is a girl I can't buy back
with a fleet of movie cars.

01:45:30.316 --> 01:45:32.580
- Oh.
- Specifically, I said "can't. "

01:45:32.752 --> 01:45:36.119
Get rid of...
Just get rid of them. It's embarrassing.

01:45:36.289 --> 01:45:39.087
- So I guess your mother forgave you.
- Yeah, yeah, you know.

01:45:39.258 --> 01:45:43.888
I got my inheritance in return
for running the Bach charity discreetly.

01:45:44.063 --> 01:45:45.963
Should we just take the subway?

01:45:47.433 --> 01:45:49.458
Which one's the fastest?

01:45:56.008 --> 01:45:58.772
Through the park, please, Bitterman.

01:45:59.305 --> 01:46:05.336
